Q: Alice, Bob, and Claire are playing a game. At the start of the game, they are each holding a ball: Alice has a yellow ball, Bob has a blue ball, and Claire has a pink ball.
As the game progresses, pairs of players trade balls. First, Claire and Alice swap balls. Then, Alice and Bob swap balls. Finally, Claire and Bob swap balls. At the end of the game, Bob has the
Options:
(A) yellow ball
(B) blue ball
(C) pink ball
A: (A)

Q: In a game of musical chairs, five people - Alice, Bob, Claire, Dave, and Eve - take turns sitting in a chair. The game starts with Alice sitting in the chair, followed by Bob, Claire, Dave, and finally Eve.
Next, the first four people - Alice, Bob, Claire, and Dave - get up and move to the right, while Eve remains in the chair. Then, the first three people - Alice, Bob, and Claire - get up and move to the right, while Dave and Eve remain in the chair. Finally, the first two people - Alice and Bob - get up and move to the right, while Claire, Dave, and Eve remain in the chair. In the end, the person sitting in the chair is
Options:
(A) Alice
(B) Bob
(C) Claire
(D) Dave
(E) Eve
A: (E)||
